
Functional Test Cases
1	Verify if a user can log in with a valid email address and password.
2   Enter the valid email address & click next. Verify if the user gets an option to enter the password.
3	Don’t enter an email address or phone number & just click the Next button. Verify if the user will get the error message
    or if the blank field will get highlighted.
4	Enter the invalid email address & click the Next button. Verify if the user will get the error  message.
5	Enter an invalid phone number & click the Next button. Verify if the user will get the error message.
6
7	Verify if a user can log in with a valid phone number and password.
8	Verify if a user cannot log in with a valid phone number and an invalid password.
9	Verify if a user cannot log in with a valid email address and a wrong password.
10	Verify the ‘Forgot email’ functionality.
11	Verify the ‘Forgot password’ functionality.
12 Verify if the ‘Enter’ key of the keyboard is working correctly on the login page.
13. Verify if a user cannot enter the characters more than the specified range in each field (Username and Password).
14. Verify that 'create account' is working fine and on clicking it, user navigated to account page

Non Functional Test cases
Verify the time taken to login
Verify the timeout functionality of the login session.
Verify the Login page against SQL injection attack.

Other Test Cases

    Verify the time taken to log in with a valid username and password.	(Performance & Positive Testing)
	Verify if the font, text color, and color coding of the Login page is as per the standard.	(UI Testing & Positive Testing
	Verify the login page and all its controls in different browsers	Browser Compatibility & Positive Testing.